In the Cartesian coordinate system $xOy$, the parametric equation of curve $C$ is $\begin{cases} & x=3\cos \alpha \\ & y=\sin \alpha \end{cases}$ ($\alpha$ is the parameter), and in the polar coordinate system with the origin as the pole and the positive $x$-axis as the polar axis, the polar equation of line $l$ is $\rho \sin (\theta -\dfrac{\pi }{4})=\sqrt{2}$.


