In the Cartesian coordinate system $xOy$, the parametric equation of line $l$ is $\begin{cases} x=3+t\cos \alpha \\ y=1+t\sin \alpha\end{cases}$ (where $t$ is the parameter), in the polar coordinate system (with the same unit length as the Cartesian coordinate system $xOy$, and the origin $O$ as the pole, and the non-negative half-axis of $x$ as the polar axis), the equation of curve $C$ is $\rho=4\cos \theta$.  
